{"key":"processedPost-12683589","value":{"id":12683589,"first":12683339,"last":12686630,"when":1275663919,"utime":"06/04/10 06:05 PM","content":"I've used the same glass lamp for quite a few years.&nbsp; I'm sure yours just got damaged in shipment or had a manufacturing defect.<br /><br />As for how much alcohol they use, not much.&nbsp; However, they'll evaporate more alcohol out between uses than is consumed during use.&nbsp; Don't fill it more than 1/4 full each time so you don't have much left over.&nbsp; Chances are, it won't still be there the next time you go to use it.<br /><br />I learned the hard way to ALWAYS have a fire extinguisher in the room at all times when using alcohol for sanitizing at the same time a lamp is burning.&nbsp; Keep the lamp and your bottle of alcohol at opposite ends of your work table, and get a dispenser for the alcohol rather than pouring it out of the bottle.&nbsp; Less will spill this way if you accidentally knock it over.<br />RR","title":"Re: Spirit/Alcohol Lamp cracked"}}